# Component Creation Rules

**Reference implementation:** `src/components/atoms/button/`

---

## How to Use This File

When creating a component, say:
```
Create a [ComponentName] component:
- Variants: [list]
- Sizes: [list]
- Features: [list]
- Base: Pressable/View

Follow component-creation.mdc
```

I'll create production-ready component following all rules below.

---

## File Structure (Mandatory)

```
src/components/atoms/{name}/
├── constants.ts    ← Config (VARIANT_CONFIG, SIZE_CONFIG, DISABLED_CONFIG)
├── types.ts        ← Union types + Props interface
├── styles.ts       ← Theme-aware styles
├── index.tsx       ← Main component (composition only)
└── __tests__/{name}.test.tsx
```

Sub-components optional: `icon-wrapper.tsx`, `indicator.tsx`, etc.

---

## 1. constants.ts - Store Values, Not Keys

```typescript
import type { ComponentVariant, ComponentSize } from './types';
import type { ViewStyle, TextStyle } from 'react-native';
import { styles } from './styles';

interface VariantConfig {
  containerStyle: ViewStyle;
  labelStyle: TextStyle;
  indicatorColor: string;
  rippleColor: string;
}

interface SizeConfig {
  containerStyle: ViewStyle;
  labelStyle: TextStyle;
  iconSize: number;
}

// ALL variant behavior in ONE place
export const VARIANT_CONFIG: Record<ComponentVariant, VariantConfig> = {
  default: {
    containerStyle: styles.variantDefault,           // ✅ Value
    labelStyle: styles.labelDefault,                 // ✅ Value
    indicatorColor: styles.labelDefault.color as string, // ✅ Value
    rippleColor: 'rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2)',        // ✅ Value
  },
  // ... other variants
};

export const SIZE_CONFIG: Record<ComponentSize, SizeConfig> = {
  default: {
    containerStyle: styles.sizeDefault,
    labelStyle: styles.label,
    iconSize: 20,
  },
  // ... other sizes
};

// Disabled overrides variant
export const DISABLED_CONFIG: VariantConfig = {
  containerStyle: styles.disabled,
  labelStyle: styles.labelDisabled,
  indicatorColor: styles.indicatorDisabled.color as string,
  rippleColor: 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05)',
};
```

**Key:** Store resolved values at module load. No runtime lookups.

